						Programmer Wows 'Em<BR/>
						Nov. 12, 2001<BR/>
						By Eileen Colkin<BR/><BR/>
						How do you get the best 256 pro and amateur programmers to compete for the title of best in the business? Offer tough programming problems-and $250,000.<BR/><BR/>
						That's how recruiting firm Top-Coder, which seeks quality programmers for its database, found Stanford University junior Jon McAlister. He won the $100,000 first prize for best programmer at the first TopCoder Invitational, held Nov. 2-3 at Foxwoods Casino and Resort in Mashantucket, Conn.<BR/><BR/>
